column3: str

<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Kohm Noskh gazes upon you with sorrowful eyes.
Slay the bellicose broodmother.
Report to Kohm Noskh.
Tiny traveler... Thou hast traversed the great expanse to stand before me. I ask thee─on thy journey, didst thou find strength?
None here have been spared the torment of loss...yet even tragedy cometh not in equal measure.
Nay, of all my kin, the broodsires feel it most deeply. Eggs crushed before their eyes, hatchlings twisted beyond recognition...they cannot be blamed for turning to madness.
One I would have you slay, for mine own power sufficeth not to end her suffering. She yet wandereth, restless, near the ash-choked lake, though naught but poison is to be found there now...
The lake lieth beyond the vitrified fort. End the broodmother's suffering, I beg thee...
Thou... Thou art the murderer of my children!
Long... So long have I been weary...
Thy countenance speaketh volumes... I thank thee.
The metal demons struck without warning... Beautiful and pitiless as falling stars.
We fought, yes... Yet for all our savagery, we failed to protect the young. What few survived emerged from their eggs disfigured and screaming...
Would that fate had taken a different course. We might have welcomed them to this world together, and guided them unto a brilliant future...
What will you say?
Midgardsormr's children live on.
There are still dragons on my star.
I have encountered young dragons in my travels.
So the young have found their place elsewhere... Our kind shall live on.
I am gladdened to hear not all was in vain. May thy path lead thee true, traveler.
